{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1468014858,"nonce":"ihHT/vKqlv8hMPESR36UTjz7X3s=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxNjQ2MjM3MDQ=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/873","origin":"github"},"title":"galaxydepot prebuilt R 3.2.1 is missing atlas: `package_r_3_2_1`","message":"The `tool_dependencies.xml` file for [`package_r_3_2_1` does not properly set the install environment for building R, missing the atlas package](https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/master/packages/package_r_3_2_1/tool_dependencies.xml#L60).\n\nUsing the prebuilt package, `package_deseq2_1_10_0` and `package_bioconductor_edger_3_14_0` both fail to install on CentOS 6 with the error: \n\n```\n/usr/bin/ld: cannot find -lblas\n```\n\nHowever, if I add the following to the `tool_dependencies.xml` file, rebuild R, then deseq2 and edger install fine.\n\n```\n\u003cpackage name=\"atlas\" version=\"3.10.2\"\u003e\n    \u003crepository changeset_revision=\"f27d2f8761ae\" name=\"package_atlas_3_10\" owner=\"iuc\" prior_installation_required=\"True\" toolshed=\"https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu\" /\u003e\n\u003c/package\u003e\n```\n\nActually, I'm not positive that adding this step is necessary, but building R certainly is.","files":null}]}